Exp – 10 

Aim 

To launch a virtual machine using TryStack (Online OpenStack Demo Platform). 
OpenStack is an open-source cloud platform used to create and manage virtual machines. TryStack 
provides a free online environment to practice OpenStack without installing any software locally. 
It allows users to launch instances (virtual machines) using the Horizon dashboard. 

Procedure 

1. Open the TryStack website in a browser.  
2. Register for a TryStack account.  
3. Login to the OpenStack Horizon dashboard.  
4. Navigate to: Compute → Instances 
5. Click on Launch Instance.  
6. Enter instance name and details.  
7. Select an image (Ubuntu Linux).  
8. Choose a flavor (RAM, CPU, storage).  
9. Configure network settings.  
10. Click Launch.  
11. Wait until instance status becomes Running.  
12. Click Console to access the virtual machine.  

Output 

The virtual machine is launched successfully and the console displays the operating system 
interface. 
